Sentencas: As a part of the research project aimed at developing a thermodynamic database of the La-Sr-Co-Fe-O system for applications in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs), the Co-Fe-O subsystem was thermodynamically re-modeled in the present work using the CALPHAD methodology.
Titulo: Thermodynamic modeling of the Co-Fe-O system

Sentencas: The solid phases were described using the Compound Energy Formalism (CEF) and the ionized liquid was modeled with the ionic two-sublattice model based on CEF.
Titulo: Thermodynamic modeling of the Co-Fe-O system

Sentencas: A set of self-consistent thermodynamic parameters was obtained eventually.
Titulo: Thermodynamic modeling of the Co-Fe-O system

Sentencas: Calculated phase diagrams and thermodynamic properties are presented and compared with experimental data.
Titulo: Thermodynamic modeling of the Co-Fe-O system

Sentencas: The modeling covers a temperature range from 298 K to 3000 K and oxygen partial pressure from 10(-16) to 10(2) bar.
Titulo: Thermodynamic modeling of the Co-Fe-O system

Sentencas: A good agreement with the experimental data was shown.
Titulo: Thermodynamic modeling of the Co-Fe-O system

Sentencas: Improvements were made as compared to previous modeling results.
Titulo: Thermodynamic modeling of the Co-Fe-O system
